U1L5

A) It will ask for input on a length and then square that number to give the area of a square
B) Please input a length: 5
The area of a square of side length 5.0 is: 25.0

C) It stopped after reaching the last line of code and my mathematical result was the same as their output
D) import math
length = input("Please input a radius: ")
length = float(length)
SqArea = 4 * math.pow((length), 2)
SemiArea = 0.5 * math.pi * math.pow(length, 2)
area = SemiArea + SqArea
area = SemiArea + SqArea
print("The area of the square and semicircle with a radius of", length, "is: %.2f" % area)

R has to be multiplied by 2 because a square uses side lengths which are equivalent to the diameter not the radius


