U1L7

A) 1. It will say Yes! 3 is a factor of 6
   2. Now deciding if 5 is a factor of 6 ... and nothing else

B/C) Yes it matched my expectations and calculations
D) import math

x = input("Please input a whole number: ")
x = int(x)
y = input("Please input another nonzero whole number ")
y = int(y)
print("Now deciding if", y, "is a factor of", x, "...")
if y != 0:
    rem = x % y
    if rem == 0:
        print("Yes!", y, "is a factor of", x)
    else:
        print("No!", y, "isn't a factor of", x)
else:
    print("I request a nonzero whole number")

E) I did this in D already

F) import math

x = input("Please input a whole number from 1-20: ")
x = int(x)
if x>0 and x<21:
    y = input("Please input another whole number from 1-20: ")
    y = int(y)
    if y>0 and 21>y:
        print("Now deciding if", y, "is a factor of", x, "...")
        if y != 0:
            rem = x % y
            if rem == 0:
                print("Yes!", y, "is a factor of", x)
            else:
                print("No!", y, "isn't a factor of", x)
        else:
            print("I request a nonzero whole number")
    else:
        print("I requested a value between 1-20")
else:
    print("I requested a value between 1-20")
